lyrics:
On the wings of the wind, a lone seagull flies,
Crossing the lagoon with a gaze both bold and wise.
Among Venice's waves, its flight sings an ode,
To the secrets of the sea, and the tales the wind has stowed.It soars past the palaces, witnesses of old,
Whispering secrets in a timeless mold.
With eyes set to the sky, and heart aflutter,
The seagull dances, in its eternal mutter.
